Message: Alright, I'm back and I have time now
So to recap my role:
Name: Will Feral
Objective: Kill all elves before the game ends
Abilities/details:
I can attack a player at night, if they are an elf or are viewed as a member of the Wolfpack, I will try to kill them. I will spare anyone else
I look like a wolf to the Seer
(I do not use Witchcraft; This is not relevant, but still a thing)
And I am night immune
I currently hold a Hvisla Rune (spent, obviously), Tarot Cards and I was just given an Altruistic Trinket
I will be giving my Rune and Tarot Cards to you and the Altruistic Trinket to Devil
What I have done every night:

N1: I tried to attack Zero, I assumed I had succeeded, but according to the GD claim, I actually didn't attack them; I used my Rune on MummyBoy (They talked a lot D1 and I wanted someone else to investigate possible elf locations); I used the Tarot Cards on Santa and got a Dove/Hound result; I passed Holy Lights (not lit) to Werewolf
Side note: I assume all the lights started with a solo non-villager (We already know me and Rude Dolph, the other(s) may have started with Bloody Holly and/or Santa Claws
N2: I tried to attack Harlequin, considering the 2 kills I assume I succeeded; I talked to MummyBoy, I used the Tarot Cards on Creature and got Magician/Death
@Shock I had a RoT, I didn't block anyone. I passed it with the Xbow I received
I was a plain villager
I was wondering if Santa Claws saw me as wp (as I could be a lycan) hence the gift

Regarding the whispers to MummyBoy: I pretended to be someone who wanted to be friends with elves and asked for their help. I then voiced my suspicion on Santa, tbh I didn't even think to say why I sussed them, I guess I just didn't want too much info about me to get out for when I would claim (the reason was however the decent chance that the Hound card was theirs + my belief that maybe the killing wolf was blocked N1 since there was only 1 death which could have been caused by me), I was completely sincere in my accusation. I also threatened that if they were a wolf, if they mess with me I'll mess with them, but if they left me alone I'd leave them alone (I have no beef with the wolves, unless they start something against me)
But they don't choose if they give bad or good presents so...
Could be a random gift
That Cyclops has my RoT now. Which makes me wonder if they're claiming NI becauss of that
Or maybe they passed idk

N3: I tried to attack MummyBoy (based on a comment on how they were drunk like an Elf or something, I had hoped that would have been a hint that they were an Elf, but nothing happened, so they are either really not an Elf/viewed as a Wolf, or they are a night immune wolf; I used my Tarot Cards on Igor and got Hound/Labourer, I passed Slay Bells to FishGirl; And finally I was Poisoned

N4: I attacked Lock, based on a suspicion that maybe the whispers they sent to Easter had to do with the sloshed thing, which I was convinced was caused by an Elf, it looks like I was successful, I used my Tarot Cards on Easter for much the same reason and got Labourer/Death; I used my Rune on you (MeltingMan) and passed the Lycan!Bloody Wreath I just got to Behemoth (The potential Elf pool was still big so I took my chance, and with their lack of activity I could justify it)

N5 (Tonight): I plan on attacking Sally, BECAUSE I am still not completely convinced Devil is an Elf and I put my objective first. If they are really an Elf then the Shield they claimed went to Bertha should show up. It's also better to have a confirmed Elf tomorrow or have a good target to lynch. Either way I'd say the Village benefits from that, perhaps more than Sally
Like I said, I'll be passing items: Tarot Cards + Rune to you (MeltingMan) and Trinket to Devil
Oh and N4 my speech was messed with of course

TO BE CLEAR: I claimed because I wanted to, I could have kept my mouth shut and taken the quiet road to victory, but I wanted to clear up the stories around the "Grinch" and talk about my role. Sally had a feeling that it was me, which did play a part in me confessing my true role, but was hardly the only cause. I did think it would come across better if I told you myself rather than being forced to

With so few elves left I felt that the village wouldn't lose that much if I killed them, since in return they'll earn my gratitude and teamwork, I like to think I've been working for the village during the day this game, I've been going around chasing leads, genuinely looking for evils (even if it was also to rule out any potential elves for me, but I never faked intel against anybody and kept demands/accusations reasonable). At this point I am very close to victory and you all are very close to gaining a valuable ally

Lynching me would probably hurt the village in the long run, since, looking at the claims, there isn't a lot of intel around, so my relatively reliable intel would be a huge asset. At that point I could hardly harm the village even if I wanted to
If you want my opinion on who is probably evil, it'd be: Barrel, Devil, Ethan and EasterBunny in that order I think
Santa is also still possible, but who knows, they're lower on my sus list
I'm legit having a lot of fun this game and I don't want it to end for me because some players can't understand that a role with up- and downsides for both village and wolves is actually Neutral

So if at any point today I seemed to get a bit heated, it's because I am telling the complete truth because I wanted to, and I genuinely want to help the village, after I take care of my own objective. But to be called "anti-evil" with a role that is clearly also not great for the village (at this point much less so, obviously) looks like the evils feel threatened and I can't help but get annoyed since that statement is just not true

After all, it is confirmed by Lock, Sally and Devil that there is something hunting elves (me), and hunting a certain group of villagers, at best is village subfaction behaviour and at worst Neutral behaviour. Evils would already need to get rid of them anyway, so having that additional objective makes no sense for them. And from that, lynching me instead of an actual evil is not very good, since you're still just bringing Village parity down, instead of evil parity
Considering numbers, at this point sacrificing 1 or 2 villagers for a Night Immune wolf killer is not too bad at all, especially when they seem very willing to help, no?
"wolf killer" meaning somebody that kills wolves, not a killing wolf, of course
Thanksfor (hopefully) reading my essay lol
I genuinely hope you don't die :)
